_header: Here is comen that no man wot
Bibliographic Ghosts: Oxford, Bodleian Library Laud misc. 568 (SC 1117), f. 43v
_description: A dialogue in a Latin nemo joke with a Latin line between the two English lines — a couplet tag in the Fasciculus morum

Bod187.Transcription:
Her ys y come þat no man wot he payth best for hys frawtrow
                    forth þe bote

BodRawC670.Transcription:
Here is comen þat no mon wot…ȝe ȝe þe
                    deuel in þy eye and row forthe þe boot
BodRawC670.Editions:
Wenzel,  Siegfried. 
             Verses in Sermons: ‘Fasciculus morum’ and Its Middle
                English Poems.
         Cambridge, MA: Medieval Academy of America, 1978: 167.
